Name: Vegetarian Paella
Description: A Spanish classic with a vegetarian twist. Bursting with vibrant vegetables, this dish is a feast for the senses.
Details: This is a family recipe passed down through generations with a healthy twist. Make sure to use fresh vegetables for the best flavor.

Name: Quinoa Salad
Description: This fresh, zingy salad is super easy and always a crowd-pleaser! The vibrant colors and flavors make it a joy to both make and eat.
Details: Perfect for a summer barbecue or a healthy lunch option. You can substitute the vegetables listed with your favorite ones.

Name: Classic French Ratatouille
Description: A hearty and healthy vegetable dish, ratatouille combines eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, and tomatoes in a basil-infused simmer that warms the home and soul.
Details: The trick to a perfect Ratatouille is to cook the vegetables separately so each will taste truly good in its own right.

Name: Spaghetti Carbonara
Description: A classic Italian pasta dish from Rome made with egg, hard cheese, guanciale, and black pepper.
Details: The dish is not made with cream. The creamy texture is achieved through the mixture of egg, cheese and pasta water.

Name: Chicken Tikka Masala
Description: A dish of chunks of roasted marinated chicken in a spiced curry sauce. The sauce is usually creamy and orange-coloured.
Details: The dish has been claimed as a national dish of the United Kingdom, and its origins are debated.

Name: Pad Thai
Description: Stir fried rice noodle dish commonly served as a street food and at most restaurants in Thailand.
Details: Pad Thai has been popular in Thailand since the 1930s when the government promoted it in an effort to reduce rice consumption.

Name: Tacos al Pastor
Description: Mexican dish featuring a pork and pineapple mix, cooked on a spit, it is served on tortillas.
Details: This dish was created in the 20th century in Puebla, Mexico by Lebanese immigrants.

Name: Japanese Ramen
Description: Noodle soup dish that was originally imported from China and has become one of the most popular dishes in Japan in recent decades.
Details: Ramen are inexpensive and widely available, two factors that also make them an ideal option for budget travelers.

Name: American Cheeseburger
Description: Classic American dish consisting of a hamburger topped with cheese and served in a bun.
Details: You can add various toppings like lettuce, tomato, mayonnaise, ketchup, and pickles. Serve with a side of fries.

Name: Sushi
Description: Japanese dish consisting of small balls or rolls of vinegar-flavoured cold rice served with a garnish of raw fish, vegetables, or egg.
Details: Sushi can be enjoyed many ways and with various ingredients, making it a versatile and delightful dish.
